A path to hypothesis

I have a question: how tickets are distributed amongst agents by language? Is there any correlation between tickets amount, language and agent whos solving a problem?

Lets try to build a graph thatll help me bate my curiosity.

From the boxplot above we can easily notice that there are some outliers which brings us to the idea that perhaps some agents prefer to take tickets in a specific language. So, my hypothesis is that there are agents that prefer a specific language of the problem they solve.

Hypothesis testing

Lets take a Pearsons Chi-squared test to see if theres any correlation between the language of a ticket and an agent who solves that ticket.


    Pearson's Chi-squared test

data:  tbl_languages
X-squared = 354.06, df = 169, p-value = 3.504e-15
You can select how Pearsons residuals values are represented:

From the table above we can conclude that some agents prefer to solve problems reported from a particular country. To be more precise, Nicole and Marlen prefer to take tickets in either Spanish or French.
